-- Spain May Reduce Share of Algerian Gas Imports, Expansion Newspaper Says
-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 2010-10-15T05:29:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/spain-may-reduce-share-of-algerian-gas-imports-expansion-newspaper-says.html
Spain’s Industry Ministry is
considering reducing the maximum share of Spanish gas imports
that any gas-supplying country can have to 30 percent from 50
percent, Expansion reported, without saying where it got the
information.  The ministry’s ability to change the limit may increase
the bargaining power of Gas Natural SDG SA in its dispute with
Algeria’s Sonatrach, Spain’s main supplier, the newspaper said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
